        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 5:31PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 531 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southwest of Wolf Creek Park, or 22 miles south of Perryton,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wolf Creek Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
